<div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br /><div class="quotetitle">Drag wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">(Also, I'm glad I wasn't the only one to force composers to specify the note length for every single note :S (glad I got rid of that in DNSF2))<br /></div><br />How else is the engine supposed to distinguish quarter notes from eighth notes? Or are you talking about a syntax that doesn't just default to sixteenth notes unless specified otherwise?</div><br />I mean, rather than have every notes be two bytes (&lt;note&gt;&lt;length&gt;), I changed it so you specify the note length once, and it applies for all following notes until you specify a new one.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=21">Drag</a> — Sat Apr 09, 2011 8:35 pm</p><hr />
